===Etymology 1===
Old English ''[[sacu]]'' "cause, lawsuit, legal action, complaint, issue, dispute", from Germanic ''*sako''. Cognate with Danish {{term|sag}}, Dutch ''[[zaak]]'' "cause, thing", German ''[[Sache]]'' "thing, legal cause", {{term|𐍃𐌰𐌺𐌾𐍉|sc=Goth|tr=sakjo|lang=got||dispute, argument}}, Swedish ''[[sak]]''.

